post, click on the title of the post, and you\'ll be taken to the blog post itself.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Participants\' Blog Posts</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a list of the blog posts mentioning the \'oped12\' keyword or tag harvested from the list of blogs submitted by participants. <br />[<a  href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?action=viewer\">Browse all Blog Posts</a>]</p>\r\n\r\n<!-- Begin Post -->\r\n\r\n<p><b><a  href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/link/803/rd\">Is the future of higher and distance education asynchronous, open and just-in-time (#oped12)?</a></b><br/>\r\n<i>opendistanceteachingandlearning, opendistanceteachingandlearning</i><br/>Just in case, just in time, just enough, just for me&#8230; What do these say about our degree structures, the time (and resources) our students need to complete full qualifications designed in a bygone era and where the reality of &#8230; Continue reading &#8594; [<a  href=\"http://opendistanceteachingandlearning.wordpress.com/2012/10/01/is-the-future-of-higher-and-distance-education-asynchronous-open-and-just-in-time-oped12/\">Link</a>]\r\nMon, 01 Oct 2012 04:56:08 +0000  \r\n [<a  href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?db=post&action=edit&autoblog=803\">Comment</a>]</p>\r\n<!-- Begin Post -->\r\n\r\n<p><b><a  href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/link/801/rd\">A Culmination of Openness Elements</a></b><br/>\r\n<i>Glenyan, A Point of Contact</i><br/>My assignment 1 for the the Openness in Education 622 course&#8230; The dictionary.com entry for the adjective form of the word open includes more than forty definitions, making it understandable why there are many elements to the term openness in education. The literature on the subject reflects these wide and varied elements, however three aspects [...] [<a  href=\"http://apointofcontact.wordpress.com/2012/10/01/a-culmination-of-openness-elements/\">Link</a>]\r\nMon, 01 Oct 2012 04:08:41 +0000  \r\n [<a  href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?db=post&action=edit&autoblog=801\">Comment</a>]</p>\r\n<!-- Begin Post -->\r\n\r\n<p><b><a  href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/link/788/rd\">I\'m still following #oped12 , but in a very loose way. Not interested in doing homework per se, b...</a></b><br/>\r\n<i>, CDATA(0)</i><br/>I\'m still following #oped12 , but in a very loose way. Not interested in doing homework per se, but I am quite interested in putting openness into practice in my teaching. To use a metaphor: I am more interested in becoming light than in talking about brightness.This week\'s topic is \"Licensing and Copyright Protection\" (http://open.mooc.ca/week3.htm). The readings and videos are quite counter-cultural; not that there\'s anything wrong with that.Nonetheless, the topic interes... [<a  href=\"https://plus.google.com/110117137800261731479/posts/YtVg6zMFqMh\">Link</a>]\r\nSun, 30 Sep 2012 13:05:30 +0200  \r\n [<a  href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?db=post&action=edit&autoblog=788\">Comment</a>]</p>\r\n<!-- Begin Post -->\r\n\r\n<p><b><a  href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/link/762/rd\">Copyright and power</a></b><br/>\r\n<i>, EdTech -  Insights</i><br/>The readings and viewings for #oped12 on openness in education Week 3 get you thinking.After watching the excellent RiP: the Remix Manifesto by Laurent LaSalle, I turned to G+ and found a What\'s Hot item. Except I could not see it. I saw this instead:Samuel L. Jackson\'s WTFU campaign for Obama had been taken down due to a copyright claim by JCER. Could this be the Jewish Council for Education and Research, the same group that produced the advert? Don\'t know.But why are they object... [<a  href=\"http://edtech-insights.blogspot.com/2012/09/copyright-and-power.html\">Link</a>]\r\nFri, 28 Sep 2012 20:41:00 +0000  \r\n [<a  href=\"http://open.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?db=post&action=edit&autoblog=762\">Comment</a>]</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>New Discussion Threads</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Consider commenting on participant\'s blog post to create a new discussion here. To view the entire di